          <lg n="1">
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-124-083Y-line-1" n="1">Now hardly here &amp; there a hackney Coach</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-083Y-line-2" n="2">Appearing, showd the ruddy morns approach.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-083Y-line-3" n="3">om.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-083Y-line-4" n="4">om.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-083Y-line-5" n="5">The slip-shod 'prentice from his masters door,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-083Y-line-6" n="6">Had par'd the street, &amp; sprinkled round the floor,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-083Y-line-7" n="7">Now Moll had whirld her mop with dextrous airs,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-083Y-line-8" n="8">Prepard to scrub the entry &amp; the stairs.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-083Y-line-9" n="9">The youth with broomy stumps began to trace,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-083Y-line-10" n="10">The kennel edge, where wheels had worn the place,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-083Y-line-11" n="11">The smallcole man was heard with cadence deep,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-083Y-line-12" n="12">Till drownd in shriller notes of chimney sweep.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-083Y-line-13" n="13">Duns at his Lord·ships gate began to meet,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-083Y-line-14" n="14">And brick·dust Moll had screamd thro half the street.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-083Y-line-15" n="15">The turnkey, now his flock returning sees,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-083Y-line-16" n="16">Duly let out a'nights to steal for fees.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-083Y-line-17" n="17">The watchful bailifs take their silent stand</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-124-083Y-line-18" n="18">And school-boys lag with satchels in their hand.</l>
          </lg>
